Your workout plan it’s important but more important it’s  your recovery after your workout. 

If you feel you’re workouts are good but don’t have great results here’s maybe why. You may not follow a good recovery plan. Make sure you’re taking care of these aspects in order to maximize your results.
.
.
☑️ Having enough protein (1 gram/ lb) 
☑️ Stay hydrated 
☑️ Sleep (7-8 h) 
☑️ Walk/ stretch/ foam rolling/ massage gun 
☑️ Give your muscles at least 72 h of rest 

.
.
If you workout and you’re still sore your body won’t allow more muscle growth, so better take couple days to fully recover and be able to have a good workout. 

You can obviously train other muscle groups, but avoid involving the ones that need recovery. If your full body is sore then definitely wait until fully recovered. 
.
.

🍑Why is your med glutes so important? 🍑

You guys remember I made a post the past days about the booty shapes. From that post I had lots of questions about the shapes, insertions, specific exercises for glutes etc. 

It was also a big conversation about the med glutes and I mentioned that I know a lot of girls who don’t like this muscle visible and they want to get rid of it. 
.
.
Again, I love my med glutes and the body shape it gives me. It has a lot of benefits not only makes your waist look smaller but it also: 
🍑 stabilizes pelvis 
🍑 stabilizes the knee (so your knee does not go inward when you’re squatting. If that happens you may have weak med glutes 🤷‍♀️) 
🍑 offers stability when walking, running, basically when you stand on one leg 
🍑 when strong reduces lower back pain 
.
.
Why you would want to get rid of the muscle that helps you move from one foot to another and offer stability ? 

The stronger your glutes the better your performance will be. 🍑🦾 
.
.
Hope this post helps and you realize how important is this little muscle 😃 now get to work! 
.
.
Ps. Because it’s such a tiny muscle it doesn’t need a tone of weight to be worked. Isolation means you want the amount of weight that muscle can take by itself. So you can easily work it with just bands or cables using light weight. The abductor machine is also a great choice! 
.
.

🔥GYM MYTHS that need to die! 💀👀

- Lifting heavy weights will make you manly 🤦🏻

- Weight loss exercises
(You can only lose weight/fat through your diet ) 🤷‍♀️

- Don’t pass your knees over your toes while squatting 🫣

- abs exercise for a flat stomach
(‼️‼️Basically by doing abs you will build muscle in your stomach area, not burning the fat. You will lose the fat through a calorie deficit. If your diet is bad and you’re doing lots of abs guess what. You are building muscle under the fat and your waist will appear even bigger. 
If you want to lose fat while working out make sure you are in calorie deficit so you don’t actually get bulky😃) 

- doing only cardio for fat loss. 
(‼️Cardio is great. And should be included in your workout routine. But not specifically for losing fat. Do cardio for your cardiovascular health and to improve your endurance and stamina. Also improves your bones health and increases your metabolism. In combination with a good diet can work great for fat loss..but not by itself)

- believing in a magic pill that will give you the results you want 🤡

- mixing exercises every week to confuse the muscle 
(If you’re working out just to keep your body moving and feel good then it’s fine. But if you want progress.. and I assume you want, then you can’t mix exercises every week. You must follow a program (4-6 exercises) for 6-8 weeks at least and try to get better at each one every week. 
Focus on better form, better range of motion, more weight, more reps with the same weight, set new PRs. Write all your sets and compare every week the progress. ) 🦾👊 

- longer workouts are more effective🥱

- stretching before working out. 
(It’s science proof that stretching more than 20 seconds per muscle group before your workout can reduce your performance) 

- you must sweat during your workout otherwise you’re not burning calories🥴

➡️Keep a strong core the whole time so you won’t use any lower back muscles.

between sets. 2-3 min before each set.
Don’t rush, take your time to execute the exercises correctly. 
➡️Remember! Muscle knows movement not numbers. So doing correctly an exercise is the most important part.

I hope this Inspire at least 1 person to start working on themselves and invest in their health. Nothing is more important in our life than to feel good with ourselves, be healthy, feel strong, love our bodies and be able to do any activities we desire and explore the world. 
Tell me how you’re going to enjoy all these if you are always feeling tired, drained, weak and with no energy? 

➡️First step is to fix your meal plan and have all the macronutrients your body needs. Second, MOVE YOUR BODY! Train, walk, run, dance, swim, bike, hike .. anything just move ! 
I choose to become more healthy through fitness because I enjoy it! You can do this through any other sport activity!  if I could do it you can too! ❤️

.
Back in 2016 when I first started working out honestly I had no idea what I was doing. I learn a lot in time, it took me years of training to get the body I have now. 
I also been through multiple phases, trying to stay lean..being afraid of getting big muscles 🥸 after I gained weight and managed to get back in shape. When we talk about progress In the gym meaning getting stronger and building muscle we have to keep in mind some things.

👀 The 4 types of pull up grip 

🦾Wide pronated grip 
🦾Close pronated grip 
🦾Neutral grip 
🦾Supinated grip ( chin ups) 

If your goal is to do pull ups you should first start at the assisted pull up machine or use a band strong enough so you’re able to do at least 3-5 reps. 

The same as every exercise you must track your progress weekly and try to do better each new week. 

🤜Staying consistent is the most important so don’t get discouraged if you’re not seeing a lot of progress at the beginning. 

It took me around 6 months to be able to do couple pull ups but of course it depends by each person strength level. Maybe you can do them in 3 months and someone else in 8 months. 
Just start and stay consistent👌🏾🦾 
.
.
Ps. The wide pull up (pronated grip) is the hardest and the supinated grip (chin ups) are the easiest. So start first with the chin ups variation and work your way up to pull ups. 
👉🏾The chin ups are easier because of the supinated grip the biceps helps during the movement. 
.

STEP UPS for Gluteeeees 🍑 are you doing them correctly? Do you feel your butt on fire during this exercise or you feel your quads and lower back? 

If you tried this exercise and don’t feel it the right way I hope this post will help you figure out the right form. 
.
.
How to perform: 

First make sure you’re core is tight and strong so you don’t involve your lower back. Just take a deep breath in your stomach and hold it on the way down and specially back on the way up ( at the top exhale and repeat). 

Focus on driving your hips in the back (basically your butt 👀) 
while controlling the movement on the way down. The  slower you go the better. 

Keep your back inclined the whole movement. Don’t come up straight (otherwise you will feel it in the quads) 
Your upper body basically doesn’t move. You stay inclined, holding the dumbbells strong with your face down and Is just your legs going down and up. (It should be called a step down because the peak tension is while going down, when the muscles lengthens) 🍑

If you feel pain in your lower back you probably are not bracing correctly or the weight is too heavy.

If you’re beginner start with just your body weight.

Work your lats and upper back muscles with these 3 exercises 🩵 

Pull ups 
I always perform the pull ups first on my back day because it’s a compound exercise that requires a lot of energy and effort. 
The main muscles that is focusing on is your lats and biceps besides all the other small and big muscles involved in the movement. 
How to perform: Squeeze your back at the top with a second pause and come down slowly allowing your lats to fully stretch. 
10 reps x4 

The Reverse fly exercises will work your upper back muscles (rhomboids) and the rear deltoid (the back part of your shoulder) 
How to perform: have the cables in the same line with your shoulder. Make sure you squeeze the back muscles and pause a second. Control the movement on the way back. If you feel only your traps during this movement just make sure you drop your shoulders. 
12-15 reps x4 

Row Machine - wide grip 
With a wide grip we are focusing more on the upper back muscles. (The muscles between your shoulders and the traps) 
How to perform: pull hard and squeeze the back pausing a second. Control the weight on the way back. 
10 reps x4

Here’s 3 common mistakes people do in the gym that slows down their progress. 

1.Not tracking their progress (weights, reps, sets, form) 
How you think you’re going to progress if you’re not tracking? 

2.Not following a workout plan and mixing up exercises each session. The only way to build muscle through an exercise is to go up in weight. And to be able to go up in weight you have to keep doing that exercise each week. To be able to remember the weight you use and the reps you do, you  need to track. 

3. Not following a meal plan for their goal. It’s easy. If you want to build be in a calorie surplus. If you want to cut/ lose fat be in a deficit. Eat enough protein and sleep 8h/ night. Cut alcohol, fast food, sodas and everything processed and watch your body change! 

Also if you want to build don’t be scared to actually eat more. Muscle is hard to build and takes time and discipline. Is also easy to lose it if you get off track. 
Overall don’t get scared to “go too hard “ in the gym, no one got big overnight 😄

STEP UPS AT THE BELT SQUAT MACHINE 🥵 
Omg these are a total killer for your glutes, hamstrings and quads!! 

Today I thought to try these and I’m obsessed with this variation. 

Why is this so great !? 
The belt squat machine cable is incredible strong and offers constant tension, on the way down and on the way up. Is so much harder than a regular cable! 

Because it was 1st time doing it I just added 10lb and was struggling to get to 10 reps because the range of motion was so high. 
The range depends by the support size you’re using but if you don’t have one you can stack up 4,5 plates and make your own. 

How to perform:

➡️1st step, Make sure your core is strong. Lean forward with your chest, while driving glutes in the back so you target more glutes! 
While performing hold yourself onto the machine, while the other arm will hold the cable in a straight position without pulling it up. When you’re working your right leg you will hold the cable with your right arm and the same with your left side. 
Make sure you are controlling the weight on the way down and connect mind-muscle with your glutes. 

Do 10 rep on each leg 3-4x 
If you’re having a belt squat machine at your gym don’t even think twice to perform this or not, you won’t regret it! 👌🏾 just make sure you’re doing it correctly and your glutes will be on fireeee! 🔥

One important thing when working out your glutes ! 🍑

➡️ TARGET ALL GLUTES INSERTIONS. 
Meaning the glute max, med and minimus. In order to build a nice shaped, strong booty you must hit all the insertions with different variation exercises that are specific for glutes and specifically for the insertion you want to target. 

With these 4 exercises you are 100% hitting all the glutes insertions! 🔥🍑

1. Hip Thrust 10-8 x4
2. B stance RDL (using the belt squat machine cable) 10 on each leg. You can also use dumbbells. 
3. Hyper extensions for glutes 10x4 (round your back on the way up for targeting upper booty/ glutes minimus) 
4.Abduction Machine 15-20 x3
